⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Close
node GDS · GDS · ⟦The Close:GDS:888410⟧

WHO   — The Close — selling as seduction
WHAT  — The parable's mechanism: every hard sell is a small study in how wanting is engineered, the seduction under the comedy.
WHERE — GDS · The Goods (2009)  Framework inputs: The Goods: Live Hard, Sell Hard (2009, dir. Neal Brennan, Gary Sanchez/Paramount Vantage); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film's deepest idea is that selling is making people want what they don't need — and the close is that idea.
HOW   — By turning charm into commerce, desire into a deal, again and again.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the art of making you want it. Master me and you can sell anything — and slowly stop being able to want anything yourself.

